girls night out<br/><br/>Why females should avoid girls night out after they are married:
<br /><br />The other night I was invited out for the night with  &quot;the girls.&quot; I told my husband that I would be home by midnight, &quot; I promise ! &quot; Well, the hours passed and the margaritas went down way too easy, Around 3 am, ( a bit loaded ) I arrived home. Just as I got into the door, the cuckoo clock in the hall started up and cuckooed 3 times. Quickly realizing my husband would probably wake up, I cuckooed another 9 times. Really proud of myself for coming up with a quick-witted solution ( even when totally smashed ), in order to escape a prolong conflict with him.
<br />The next morning my husband asked me what time I got in, and I told him midnight. He did not seem pissed off at all. Whew ! Got away with that one ! Then he said, &quot;We need a new cuckoo clock.&quot; When I asked him why, he said. &quot; Well, last night our clock cuckooed three times, then said &quot;OH SHIT.&quot; cuckooed 4 more times, cleared it's throat, cuckooed 3 more times, giggled, cuckooed twice more, tripped over the coffee table and then farted.&quot;
